Implementation Principles:

- Before modifying an original ExecuTorch file, first check whether the feature can be implemented through a wrapper, adapter, overlay file, external script, or patch.
- Add new project-specific functionality in separate directories or overlay files whenever possible.
- If an upstream ExecuTorch file must be modified, keep the change minimal and structure it so it can be maintained as a patch and reapplied to future ExecuTorch versions.
- Do not commit build outputs, generated files, third-party artifacts, or large binaries.
- When updating ExecuTorch, prefer applying this project's overlays and patches on top of a clean upstream checkout instead of merging the entire upstream repository.
- Write README and setup documents around the practical flow: clone ExecuTorch, apply overlays or patches, then build and run.
- Continuously update `my_research/foundation/docs/for_cursor_llm.md` when implementing features, changing project structure, fixing errors, or making workflow decisions. Record what changed, why it changed, and any errors/fixes that future agents should know.
